narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Don't wait to take it. Get it over with. And find an instructor that speaks English.
Not too bad, though most people who have taken this course have already taken Calculus it seems. That can be tricky.

Very standard calc class; it was basically the same thing as my AP calc AB class in high school. There weren't any surprise and considering this course is a prerequisite to many majors, it's definitely worth taking freshman year when calc is still fresh from high school.

I would summarize it as learning derivatives and their applications as well as touching on integrals. I would recommend this course to another student as it is very comprehensive and the applications are useful.
Equivalent to Calc AB, good intro course if interested in taking higher level math.
A straightforward introductory calc class. Take it if you're interested in gaining a firmer grasp on the basics before moving on to more complicated material.
